<module>
  <title>tòisich</title>
  <p><strong>tòisich</strong> is a (regular) verb corresponding to the English <en>start, begin, commence</en>.</p>
  <hr/>
  <p>The main usage patterns of <strong>tòisich</strong> are –</p>
  <ol>
    <li>intransitive – <mark>tòisichidh mi a-màireach</mark> <en>I will start tomorrow</en> <boxlink ref="#intransitive"/></li>
    <li><strong>tòisich a’ dèanamh rud</strong> <en>begin to do something</en> – 
      <mark>thòisich mi a’ sgrìobhadh leabhair ùir</mark> <en>I began to write a new book</en> <boxlink ref="#ag"/></li>
    <li><strong>tòisich air rud</strong> <en>start something</en> <boxlink ref="#air"/></li>
  </ol>
  <p>cf. <en>stop, finish</en>, <en>continue, keep on</en></p>
  
